
Samenvattend: de juiste vorm voor jou

() -> jobexecservice.start(workflowid) <--- is een afkeur binnen jobrunr >= versie 7

✔️ Recurring job
	•	kort
	•	non-blocking
	•	alleen trigger

✔️ WorkflowExecutionService
	•	maakt workflowExecId
	•	enqueue’t WorkflowRunner
	•	returnt meteen

✔️ WorkflowRunner
	•	doet het zware werk
	•	sequentieel / parallel
	•	wacht op nodes (polling / future)

⸻

Concrete code (zoals het moet)

WorkflowScheduleRegistrar

jobScheduler.scheduleRecurrently(
    "workflow-" + workflowId,
    cron,
    workflowStartJob::triggerWorkflow,
    workflowId
);

@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class WorkflowStartJob {

    private final WorkflowExecutionService executionService;

    @Job(name = "Trigger workflow execution")
    public void triggerWorkflow(UUID workflowId) {
        executionService.startExecution(workflowId);
    }
}
